page.title: 10FENBELLS,FENSTANTON
page.content: In the beginning{Mrs Catterick} went to a Harvest Supper at the Church Centre in 1978 and a group of people from Sawston bought some very old {handbells.} Mrs Catterick thought to her self she would like to play{handbells. The first thing Mrs Catterick had to do was to get a group and raise some money,to order some{handbells. The{12 Bells arrived in 1980. The very first time the{Fenbells {performed in public}was here at the {Fenstanton School Fete on the 6th of {June 1980. Mrs Catterick kept on adding to her set of Fenbells and now she has got{25 handbells.}The smallest bells cost about{Â£90}and the biggest bell cost about{Â£200. {Children from the School play in {the group.
